Renegade tribesmen on Wednesday ended a blockade of a strategic road in southwestern Pakistan where a gunbattle with security forces last month left about 60 people dead.
Four policemen were injured on Tuesday when they tried to remove a bomb from a railway track shortly after a blast nearby damaged the line in the restive region.
Baluchistan has been gripped by a sporadic tribal revolt for more than a year but the violence surged in January after rebels launched a deadly rocket barrage on a major gas plant in revenge for the rape of a female doctor.
